<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7492842-deb-cornell"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7492842-deb-cornell">Deb Cornell</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">What constitutes being a mother or a family? This book looked at motherhood and family in many ways and I think that theme alone would give most book <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">What constitutes being a mother or a family? This book looked at motherhood and family in many ways and I think that theme alone would give most book clubs enough to chew on. Mia's artist gift was being about to put her insight into her creations. Was Mia's gift a result of her experiences or her experiences a consequence of her gift? I really enjoyed the book and all the layers. I think the "typical middle class suburb" which you didn't care for was exactly the setting necessary to juxtapose Mia's character. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
