<div id="review_3677824210" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3677824210" />
    <a title="Nicole" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40997852-nicole"><img alt="Nicole" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642272137p2/40997852.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3677824210?book_show_action=true">Dec 16, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nicole" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nicole" href="/user/show/40997852-nicole">Nicole</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780349142920" href="/book/show/36509779-little-fires-everywhere">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40997852-nicole?shelf=2020">2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40997852-nicole?shelf=audiobooks">audiobooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40997852-nicole?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3677824210" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4131931093650861829"><b>3.5 stars</b><br/><br/>I listened to the audiobook. It was the right choice. I’m pretty sure I wouldn’t have liked it as much if I read the book. The pace was slow and I usually prefer a faster pace in this, but for some reason, I don’t mind a slow pace in audiobooks (to an extent). <br/><br/>The book is told from several points of view or rather, the narrator was telling what was happening with several people. They know the future and the past of all of the characters. Kind of omniscient. It worked well for the book.<br/><br/>T</span>
  <span id="freeText4131931093650861829" style="display:none"><b>3.5 stars</b><br /><br />I listened to the audiobook. It was the right choice. I’m pretty sure I wouldn’t have liked it as much if I read the book. The pace was slow and I usually prefer a faster pace in this, but for some reason, I don’t mind a slow pace in audiobooks (to an extent). <br /><br />The book is told from several points of view or rather, the narrator was telling what was happening with several people. They know the future and the past of all of the characters. Kind of omniscient. It worked well for the book.<br /><br />The characters were real, flawed, annoying sometimes, and I did care about some but honestly, I’m not sure what the author wanted us to make of Mia, the good guy? Well, in my opinion, she made some messed up choices and I don’t think her better than the rest. What I appreciated the most about her was how she trusted and treated Pearl. <br />Not that it matters, the realistic quality of the characters is why I liked this book. Like many others, I also wish we got more of a closure. It’s not what I call an open ending but I wanted to know the fate of some characters.<br /><br />I’m also glad I didn’t read it during the hype back in 2017 because I would’ve enjoyed it a lot less. Still, it’s not something I’d remember and not much will stay with me, hence why I rounded it up to 3 stars instead of 4 like I originally did.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4131931093650861829" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


