<div id="review_2604664677" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2604664677" />
    <a title="Erin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17957823-erin"><img alt="Erin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1597778686p2/17957823.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2604664677?book_show_action=true">Nov 25, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erin" href="/user/show/17957823-erin">Erin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/34331079-little-fires-everywhere">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17957823-erin?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17957823-erin?shelf=bookclub">bookclub</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2604664677" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12105406499080343632">So I joined a bookclub! This was our November choice and out of our eight participants-only 3( including yours truly) showed up. My did we have a grand chat over our coffees and teas this afternoon! Onward to my review...<br/> <br/><i>Little Fires Everywhere </i> takes place in the 1990&apos;s when Bill Clinton was in the White House and the utopian like community of Shaker Heights gets more than a bit shaken up by a few sets of mothers and daughters. <br/><br/>What I thought: <br/>First, I totally can join the long line of readers</span>
  <span id="freeText12105406499080343632" style="display:none">So I joined a bookclub! This was our November choice and out of our eight participants-only 3( including yours truly) showed up. My did we have a grand chat over our coffees and teas this afternoon! Onward to my review...<br /> <br /><i>Little Fires Everywhere </i> takes place in the 1990's when Bill Clinton was in the White House and the utopian like community of Shaker Heights gets more than a bit shaken up by a few sets of mothers and daughters. <br /><br />What I thought: <br />First, I totally can join the long line of readers that have stated that Ng has written an <b>engrossing</b> story that made it hard to set down so I could get my teacher planning done( I did manage to focus on the periodic table for a good 90 minutes). My biggest concentration which formed the majority of our discussion this afternoon was how deeply personal we all reacted to the various mother-daughter relationships. Since we were all women, much of our discussion revolved around good mothering and what is motherhood. Now my two buddies are both mothers, but I am not and I shared my discomfort that Ng focuses so much on the biological side. I wish my pal who adopted her two children had been there because I would certainly have appreciated her point of view. <br /><br />Aside from that point, we all decided that none of us would really fit into the Shaker Heights community as we're all Izzys</span>
  <a data-text-id="12105406499080343632" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


