<div id="review_2948897567" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2948897567" />
    <a title="Debbie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41918078-debbie"><img alt="Debbie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1594390250p2/41918078.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2948897567?book_show_action=true">Jan 13, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Debbie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Debbie" href="/user/show/41918078-debbie">Debbie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook " href="/book/show/54467912-little-fires-everywhere">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41918078-debbie?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41918078-debbie?shelf=2021-reads">2021-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41918078-debbie?shelf=contemporary-fiction">contemporary-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2948897567" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16138253495643564043">Told from several different viewpoints, I thought the characters were well-developed. Sometimes I could understand where they were coming from, and sometimes I lacked sympathy for them. I did enjoy the descriptions of Mia&apos;s artwork throughout the story. This story is plausible with a little extra titillating drama thrown in for good measure. Although the ending seemed to be left hanging, it was satisfying to me.<br/><br/>Overall, I liked this audiobook (fine narration!); however, I never watched the TV mi</span>
  <span id="freeText16138253495643564043" style="display:none">Told from several different viewpoints, I thought the characters were well-developed. Sometimes I could understand where they were coming from, and sometimes I lacked sympathy for them. I did enjoy the descriptions of Mia's artwork throughout the story. This story is plausible with a little extra titillating drama thrown in for good measure. Although the ending seemed to be left hanging, it was satisfying to me.<br /><br />Overall, I liked this audiobook (fine narration!); however, I never watched the TV mini-series. I <i>could</i> easily picture Reece Witherspoon as Elena Richardson - that role would have been well-cast!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16138253495643564043" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
